title: For Sale:  Weatherby Mark V Deluxe .340 Magnum
postcontent:
Deluxe "AA fancy" grade walnut Monte Carlo raised comb stock with rosewood forend and pistol grip cap and maplewood spacers. Fine line checkering. High lustre blued metal. 26" barrel. Factory Weatherby butt pad. Leupold Vari-X III 2.5 X 8 Gold Ring scope. Leupold mount. Leather sling believed to be factory. Scope was put on when the rifle was new. Weatherby's during this time period were made in Japan. This was considered to be first-rate equipment when my dad bought it new. Serial number indicates the rifle was made in 1989.

This rifle has been sitting in my dad's closet for quite some time. He is getting on in years and recently decided to thin the herd. He did shoot one elk with this rifle in the early 1990's. He is the only owner. He purchased it new in Southern Oregon from the now defunct Seiber's Sporting Goods. 

Rifle is in very good condition. No rust. No stock dings. But it has been sitting for years and will need to be thoroughly cleaned before use. Don't know when the last time it was fired. My dad doesn't think this rifle has had more than one box of shells (20 rounds) put through it in the last 20 years. If you are looking for a .340 Mag, then you already know about the power and energy at long range this caliber produces. 

In the April 2015 issue of Guns & Ammo, professional hunter Craig Boddington says of this rifle: "The longest shot I ever made on a grizzly was a bit over 250 yards with a .340 Weatherby Magnum; the bear never knew what hit it."

Compare my price and condition with others out there. If you were to buy this same package today, you would spend around $2400 for the rifle alone. And another $600 for the scope and mounts. Look at the gun auction websites and you will see that my rifle is hundreds of dollars less than any others.

Give me a call if you would like to talk. I have more photos that are too large for Armslist. Will gladly ship to your FFL. The rifle will be professionally packaged in bubble wrap and shipped UPS Ground. I have eleven rounds of factory Weatherby ammo that I will include with the rifle ($55 value).

Randy REDACTED
